🔧 Environment Variables Details

Required Variables

BOT_TOKEN

· Description: Telegram Bot Token from @BotFather
· How to get:
  1. Message @BotFather on Telegram
  2. Send /newbot
  3. Follow instructions
  4. Copy the token
· Example: 1234567890:ABCdefGHIjklMNOpqrsTUVwxyz

ADMIN_IDS

· Description: Telegram User IDs of admins (comma-separated)
· How to get:
  1. Message @userinfobot on Telegram
  2. Send /start
  3. Copy your ID
· Example: 123456789 or 123456789,987654321

Optional Variables

API_ID & API_HASH

· Description: Telegram API credentials (for testing)
· How to get:
  1. Visit my.telegram.org
  2. Login with your phone number
  3. Go to "API Development Tools"
  4. Create new application
· Default: API_ID=6, API_HASH=your_api_hash_here

RATE_LIMIT

· Description: Maximum generations per user
· Default: 3
· Range: 1 to 10

RATE_LIMIT_PERIOD

· Description: Rate limit reset period (seconds)
· Default: 300 (5 minutes)
· Range: 60 to 3600

SESSION_TIMEOUT

· Description: Inactive session timeout (seconds)
· Default: 300 (5 minutes)
· Range: 60 to 3600

LOG_LEVEL

· Description: Logging verbosity
· Options: DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR
· Default: INFO

PORT & HOST

· Description: Web server configuration
· Default: PORT=5000, HOST=0.0.0.0

